Refactor: Update has_modification function to use subprocess for checking git status

Why: The existing implementation used os and os.system which is not recommended for executing external commands. Refactoring to use subprocess is a better and more secure approach.

Changes:
- Removed usage of os and os.system
- Added import statement for subprocess
- Implemented subprocess to run 'git status --porcelain' command for checking modifications
- Improved handling of the command output and returning either True or False based on the result

# Veuillez saisir le message de validation pour vos modifications. Les lignes
# commençant par '#' seront ignorées, et un message vide abandonne la validation.
#
# Sur la branche main
# Votre branche est en avance sur 'origin/main' de 2 commits.
#   (utilisez "git push" pour publier vos commits locaux)
#
# Modifications qui seront validées :
#	modifié :         git/status.py
#
